article.description: Junior Robinson scored 19 points on 7-of-12 shooting and Mount St. Mary's held off St. Francis Brooklyn 55-47 on Saturday.
article.headline: Mount St. Mary's stifles St. Francis in 55-47 win
article.linkText: Mount St. Mary's stifles St. Francis in 55-47 win
article.story: NEW YORK -- Junior Robinson scored 19 points on 7-of-12 shooting and Mount St. Mary's held off St. Francis Brooklyn 55-47 on Saturday. Elijah Long added 11 points for Mount St. Mary's (9-12, 7-1 Northeast Conference), which has won five straight games. The Mountaineers stifled the Terriers defensively the entire game, holding them to 31.1 percent shooting and 5 of 19 from 3-point land. It is the second consecutive game and fourth time this year St. Francis has been held below 50 points. Rasheem Dunn led the Terriers (4-17, 2-6) with 12 points and nine rebounds. Mount St. Mary's led by six at halftime and lengthened it to nine on a Robinson 3 11 seconds into the second half. The Mountaineers held St. Francis at arm's length the rest of the way. Glenn Sanabria managed to get the Terriers to within five late, but a Robinson jumper and Long free throw put the game away.
